        "description": "QR Code Link to This Post Lexington Village Apartments 32000 Concord Drive, Madison Heights, MI, 48071 Want more information on this unit? See link (below): https://wwwbeztakcom.gotoapt.com/i2guht Call Now - show contact info x 177 OR Text 177 to show contact info to contact our leasing team. APARTMENTS IN MADISON HEIGHTS 2 Bedroom, 1 Bath | Approximately 850 Sq. Ft. Community Info: NOW OPEN! BRAND NEW COMMUNITY CENTER featuring an expansive Social Gathering Room, fitness center with state-of-the art fitness equipment and flat screen televisions and a beautifully designed outdoor swimming pool. At Lexington Village Apartments you'll find so much more than a place to call home. It begins with a walk around our beautifully landscaped grounds. The brick-faced buildings and lush green grassy areas are the perfect place to relax with your favorite four-legged friend. In addition to being close to a dog park, Lexington Village Apartments is also one of the few communities with a pet friendly policy. Better still is our location. Within walking distance of the Oakland Mall and close to downtown Royal Oak, our residents are close to great shopping, dining options and entertainment, while still enjoying the serenity of our neighborhood. Easy access to I-75 and I-696 allow neighbors an easy way to get anywhere within the city. We encourage you to visit and see for yourself just how much Lexington Village Apartments has to offer, including our unique 24-hour service guarantee. Call to set up a private tour today!   Unit Highlights ✧  Spacious closets ✧  Common laundry room in each building with full size washer and dryer ✧  On-site resident storage included ✧  Updated lighting throughout the apartment home ✧  Gas range in all apartment homes ✧  Individually-controlled air conditioning units ✧  Dishwashers available in select homes ✧  Large picturesque windows fitted with designer selected blinds ✧  Spacious living room and bedrooms featuring plush neutral carpet ✧  Brick buildings and traditional architecture ✧  Heated hallways ✧  Gas/heat, water, and trash included in flat monthly rate ✧  Walk-in closets in select homes ✧  Well-designed floor plans ranging from 625 to 850 square feet ✧  Indoor mailboxes ✧  Beautiful courtyard views available Community Highlights ✧  On-site resident storage ✧  Flex rental payments ✧  Easy access to I-75 and I-696 ✧  Updater application ✧  Controlled access and intercom system for building entry ✧  Professional onsite management team ✧  Community laundry facility with industrial sized machines ✧  Covered parking ✧  State-of-the-art fitness center with flat screen televisions ✧  Online resident portal ✧  24-hour maintenance response guarantee ✧  Package receiving ✧  Expansive community clubhouse ✧  BILT payment center ✧  Walking distance to AMC Theater and Oakland Mall ✧  Pet friendly community with well-designed pet area and less than a mile away from city dog park ✧  Beautiful, mature landscape Office Hours Monday: 9:00AM-6:00PM Tuesday: 9:00AM-7:00PM Wednesday: 9:00AM-6:00PM Thursday: 9:00AM-7:00PM Friday: 9:00AM-6:00PM Saturday: 10:00AM-6:00PM Sunday: 10:00AM-2:00PM Pet Policy Lexington Village Apartments offers pet friendly apartments in Madison Heights and welcomes both cats and dogs. You'll find beautiful green spaces where your dog can run and play. In addition, your dog can run free and meet new friends at the nearby Red Oak Dog Park. We are one of the few communities in the area to welcome your large dog! We have a limit of 2 pets under 25 lbs each or one large pet without a weight limit. Some breed restrictions apply. We're confident your pet will love living at Lexington Village Apartments as much as our human neighbors do! Income Requirements Application Requirements: Verification of Employment/Monthly Income Resident needs approximately 2.5x rent in gross monthly income based on hours worked. Co-signor needs at least 5x rent in gross monthly income ? 1 Months' worth of most recent paycheck stubs ? Or offer letter on company letterhead, typed, with starting date, and monthly income ? Confirmation of Landlord/Rental History (we review the last 2 years) ? Credit Check and Criminal Background with YARDI screening ? Application reviewed by management Equal Housing Opportunity TTw3qfoZ",
