        "description": "QR Code Link to This Post Beds: 2 Baths: 1 Square Feet: 850 Interested In This Unit? Use this link for more details: https://wwwbeztakcom.gotoapt.com/a85j3p APARTMENTS IN MADISON HEIGHTS Call Now - show contact info x 174 OR Text 174 to show contact info for more information.   Community Info NOW OPEN! BRAND NEW COMMUNITY CENTER featuring an expansive Social Gathering Room, fitness center with state-of-the art fitness equipment and flat screen televisions and a beautifully designed outdoor swimming pool. At Lexington Village Apartments you'll find so much more than a place to call home. It begins with a walk around our beautifully landscaped grounds. The brick-faced buildings and lush green grassy areas are the perfect place to relax with your favorite four-legged friend. In addition to being close to a dog park, Lexington Village Apartments is also one of the few communities with a pet friendly policy. Better still is our location. Within walking distance of the Oakland Mall and close to downtown Royal Oak, our residents are close to great shopping, dining options and entertainment, while still enjoying the serenity of our neighborhood. Easy access to I-75 and I-696 allow neighbors an easy way to get anywhere within the city. We encourage you to visit and see for yourself just how much Lexington Village Apartments has to offer, including our unique 24-hour service guarantee. Call to set up a private tour today! Residence Features ✩  Gas/heat, water, and trash included in flat monthly rate ✩  Updated lighting throughout the apartment home ✩  Large picturesque windows fitted with designer selected blinds ✩  Gas range in all apartment homes ✩  Well-designed floor plans ranging from 625 to 850 square feet ✩  Individually-controlled air conditioning units ✩  On-site resident storage included ✩  Common laundry room in each building with full size washer and dryer ✩  Walk-in closets in select homes ✩  Spacious closets ✩  Brick buildings and traditional architecture ✩  Beautiful courtyard views available ✩  Dishwashers available in select homes ✩  Spacious living room and bedrooms featuring plush neutral carpet ✩  Heated hallways ✩  Indoor mailboxes Community Features ✩  Walking distance to AMC Theater and Oakland Mall ✩  Flex rental payments ✩  Online resident portal ✩  BILT payment center ✩  Beautiful, mature landscape ✩  Package receiving ✩  Professional onsite management team ✩  Expansive community clubhouse ✩  Pet friendly community with well-designed pet area and less than a mile away from city dog park ✩  Updater application ✩  Easy access to I-75 and I-696 ✩  State-of-the-art fitness center with flat screen televisions ✩  24-hour maintenance response guarantee ✩  Community laundry facility with industrial sized machines ✩  Controlled access and intercom system for building entry ✩  Covered parking ✩  On-site resident storage Pet Policy Lexington Village Apartments offers pet friendly apartments in Madison Heights and welcomes both cats and dogs. You'll find beautiful green spaces where your dog can run and play. In addition, your dog can run free and meet new friends at the nearby Red Oak Dog Park. We are one of the few communities in the area to welcome your large dog! We have a limit of 2 pets under 25 lbs each or one large pet without a weight limit. Some breed restrictions apply. We're confident your pet will love living at Lexington Village Apartments as much as our human neighbors do! Income Requirements Application Requirements: Verification of Employment/Monthly Income Resident needs approximately 2.5x rent in gross monthly income based on hours worked. Co-signor needs at least 5x rent in gross monthly income ? 1 Months' worth of most recent paycheck stubs ? Or offer letter on company letterhead, typed, with starting date, and monthly income ? Confirmation of Landlord/Rental History (we review the last 2 years) ? Credit Check and Criminal Background with YARDI screening ? Application reviewed by management Office Hours Monday: 9:00AM-6:00PM Tuesday: 9:00AM-7:00PM Wednesday: 9:00AM-6:00PM Thursday: 9:00AM-7:00PM Friday: 9:00AM-6:00PM Saturday: 10:00AM-6:00PM Sunday: 10:00AM-2:00PM Equal Housing Opportunity gNzLhw2hx",
